---
import ContactCTA from '../components/ContactCTA.astro';
import Hero from '../components/Hero.astro';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About | Bruno Zub" description="About Bruno Zub">
	<div class="stack gap-20">
		<main class="wrapper about">
			<Hero
				title="About"
				tagline="Thanks for stopping by. Read below to learn more about myself and my background."
			>
				<img
					width="1553"
					height="873"
					src="/assets/at-work.jpg"
					alt="Bruno Zub"
				/>
			</Hero>

			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Background</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p>
						Hi, I’m Bruno Zub. I’m moving into a full-time IT career after taking the scenic route, trading traditional classrooms for hands-on, real-world experience.
					</p>
					<p>
						I’m originally from Brazil, where I started out in civil engineering at 17. That experience gave me a great foundation for breaking down complex problems, but I eventually realised the field just wasn't for me. My love for exploration (and a desire to master English) led me to London, where I ended up building a career in professional video editing.
					</p>
					<p>
						That industry was a masterclass in how to communicate clearly, manage chaos, hit unforgiving deadlines, and explain technical concepts to clients in plain English. The freedom of that career eventually led me back across the ocean to Argentina, where I added Spanish to my toolkit.
					</p>
					<p>
						If my background proves anything, it’s that I know how to drop into the deep end, figure things out, and thrive. Now, I’m pointing all that adaptability directly at IT infrastructure.
					</p>
					<p>
						I’m entirely self-taught. I spend my days in my homelab automating systems, untangling networking issues, and diving deep into Linux, Docker, Proxmox, and the Cloud. Not just reading documentation, but actually deploying things and breaking them on purpose just to learn how to fix them from the ground up.
					</p>
					<p>
						I bring a decade of experience managing clients, navigating roadblocks, and finding creative solutions without hand-holding. I’m now looking for a team where I can bring that autonomy and grit to real-world infrastructure.
					</p>
					<p>
						When I’m able to pull myself away from the screen, you can find me cycling, slowly losing the battle against my gaming backlog, or trying to convince my cat that my keyboard isn't her bed.
					</p>
					<p>
						Have a look around. Always down to swap notes on a project or talk shop about homelabs. If you’re looking for a fresh perspective for your team, I’m currently open to new opportunities and would love to hear from you.
					</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Technical Skills</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<ul>
						<li><strong>Infrastructure & OS:</strong> Linux (Debian/Ubuntu), Windows Server (Active Directory), GCP, AWS (EC2, S3)</li>
						<li><strong>Virtualization & Containers:</strong> Proxmox VE (HA, Clustering), Docker, Docker Compose, LXC</li>
						<li><strong>Networking & Security:</strong> VLANs, DNS/DHCP Administration, Zero Trust (Wireguard, Tailscale), Cloudflare Tunnels, Reverse Proxies (Nginx, HAProxy)</li>
						<li><strong>Storage & Databases:</strong> ZFS (RAIDZ, Snapshots), NFS/SMB, MariaDB/MySQL</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Education & Certifications</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p><strong>Certifications & Specialised Training</strong></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Google IT Support Professional Certificate</li>
						<li>Completed Training: CompTIA A+ Curriculum, Juniper Networking Technology Foundations</li>
					</ul>
					<br/>
					<p><strong>Universidade Positivo</strong> | <em>Curitiba, Brazil (2010 – 2015)</em></p>
					<p>Coursework in Civil Engineering</p>
				</div>
			</section>
			<section>
				<h2 class="section-title">Experience</h2>
				<div class="content">
					<p><strong>Freelance Video Editor & Business Owner</strong> | <em>2015 – Present</em></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Managed an independent freelance business, handling end-to-end project lifecycles for a diverse client base ranging from individual creators to large corporate clients.</li>
						<li>Acted as the primary point of contact, translating vague creative requests into concrete, technical deliverables.</li>
						<li>Built a reputation for strict deadline management, clear communication, and navigating complex iterative feedback loops.</li>
					</ul>
					<br/>
					<p><strong>Civil Engineering (Project Management & Planning)</strong> | <em>MRV Engenharia & DER/PR (2012 – 2015)</em></p>
					<ul>
						<li>Coordinated vertical construction processes and guided on-site teams to ensure strict quality control and productivity standards.</li>
						<li>Participated in the scheduling, planning, and execution of large-scale projects, including serving on the engineering team for a model project recognized for its cost and schedule efficiency.</li>
						<li>Managed monthly physical and financial monitoring, tracking project budgets, contractor deliverables, and operational metrics.</li>
					</ul>
				</div>
			</section>
		</main>

		<ContactCTA />
	</div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
	.about {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 3.5rem;
	}

	img {
		margin-top: 1.5rem;
		border-radius: 1.5rem;
		box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
	}

	section {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 0.5rem;
		color: var(--gray-200);
	}

	.section-title {
		grid-column-start: 1;
		font-size: var(--text-xl);
		color: var(--gray-0);
	}

	.content {
		grid-column: 2 / 4;
	}

	.content :global(a) {
		text-decoration: 1px solid underline transparent;
		text-underline-offset: 0.25em;
		transition: text-decoration-color var(--theme-transition);
	}

	.content :global(a:hover),
	.content :global(a:focus) {
		text-decoration-color: currentColor;
	}

	@media (min-width: 50em) {
		.about {
			display: grid;
			grid-template-columns: 1fr 60% 1fr;
		}

		.about > :global(:first-child) {
			grid-column-start: 2;
		}

		section {
			display: contents;
			font-size: var(--text-lg);
		}
	}
</style>
